cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper deals with learning graphical models from data using sparse logistic regression, which is a popular technique in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves analyzing the sample complexity of the algorithm, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of convex optimization and statistical guarantees suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the experimental results presented in the paper involve real-world datasets, which could place it under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
